00:09:20.170 --> 00:09:24.240
What are invisible illness
and chronic disabilities?

00:09:28.490 --> 00:09:32.590
We are confronted with the
reality that invisible illness

00:09:32.590 --> 00:09:36.660
and chronic disabilities
are often overlooked.

00:09:36.660 --> 00:09:42.590
And these conditions are
not immediately apparent.

00:09:42.590 --> 00:09:50.140
They lurk into the shadows unseen,
and they do not announce themselves

00:09:50.140 --> 00:09:52.500
with visible signs.

00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:57.790
Like, you don't see any
crutches or a wheelchair.

00:09:57.790 --> 00:09:59.220
You can't see them.

00:09:59.220 --> 00:10:02.880
And that's why we are
talking about invisible,

00:10:02.880 --> 00:10:08.200
because it's not that obvious
that someone is facing a condition

00:10:08.200 --> 00:10:13.280
which is not apparent to anyone.

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:21.449
Also, they include conditions
like chronic fatigue syndrome,

00:10:21.450 --> 00:10:27.290
and the exhaustion which
comes with chronic fatigue,

00:10:27.290 --> 00:10:33.100
but also the silent battles
of mental health conditions,

00:10:33.100 --> 00:10:37.900
as well as complex challenges
of neurological conditions.

00:10:37.900 --> 00:10:41.750
And like also having
autoimmune diseases,

00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:46.240
and you don't have any prediction
how is your day tomorrow,

00:10:46.240 --> 00:10:49.080
and how do you feel
in the next hour.

00:10:49.080 --> 00:10:56.870
For instance, I need to pace
myself to power through my day.

00:10:58.050 --> 00:11:00.190
And sometimes I
need to take breaks.

00:11:00.190 --> 00:11:06.200
And there's so much
we have to cover,

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:10.810
that a lot of people don't
understand what it means

00:11:10.810 --> 00:11:15.750
to face an invisible condition
and health condition.

00:11:19.520 --> 00:11:23.490
How do these condition
impact event participation?

00:11:23.490 --> 00:11:30.300
I'm someone who’s really
interested in attending WordCamps,

00:11:30.300 --> 00:11:36.270
and I also face a lot of
struggles when attending WordCamps

00:11:36.270 --> 00:11:38.600
because of my health conditions.

00:11:38.600 --> 00:11:45.950
And I like to explore what
it means to attend these.

00:11:45.950 --> 00:11:48.230
For instance, energy levels.

00:11:50.180 --> 00:11:54.370
I don't know if you know
about the spoon theory?

00:11:54.370 --> 00:12:00.910
When someone say, I just have
only three spoons left in a day.

00:12:00.910 --> 00:12:08.910
It is meant to be that we have to
pace ourselves and be really careful

00:12:08.980 --> 00:12:10.540
about our energy levels.

00:12:10.540 --> 00:12:18.540
Imagine charging of your smartphone
when it runs really low on battery.

00:12:20.800 --> 00:12:24.830
So you have to be very
careful of what are you doing

00:12:24.830 --> 00:12:32.830
with your fully charged,
or half-full charged mobile phone.

00:12:33.120 --> 00:12:38.850
It is also the individual journey
through a WordPress event.

00:12:38.850 --> 00:12:45.550
It is because we have a kind of
silent dance of energy with apps

00:12:45.550 --> 00:12:46.980
and flows.

00:12:46.980 --> 00:12:49.590
But it is not visible to anyone.

00:12:49.590 --> 00:12:54.610
The same goes with
sensory sensitivity.

00:12:55.840 --> 00:13:02.540
Imagine you have a bright light
on the ceiling, and it reflects

00:13:02.540 --> 00:13:09.110
on your glasses for instance,
and it's really sharp in the eyes.

00:13:10.690 --> 00:13:15.010
And this is also an
overwhelming cascade

00:13:15.010 --> 00:13:19.320
when you also have sensory
overload, not only from lights,

00:13:19.320 --> 00:13:21.040
but also from sounds.

00:13:21.040 --> 00:13:25.880
If a sound is echoing in the
room, or there is too much chatter

00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:29.040
around you, and you need
to focus on what the person

00:13:29.040 --> 00:13:30.500
in front of you is saying.

00:13:32.080 --> 00:13:39.230
Yes, that's also the sensitivity,
reflecting on clothes

00:13:39.230 --> 00:13:43.780
that you are wearing on that day,
which can also give something

00:13:43.780 --> 00:13:45.220
on top on the cascade.

00:13:46.530 --> 00:13:49.520
Now, onto the cognitive challenges.

00:13:49.520 --> 00:13:53.560
I'll just like to explore
the issues like anxiety

00:13:53.560 --> 00:14:00.070
or other cognitive aspects that
are not obvious to everyone.

00:14:00.070 --> 00:14:03.990
But someone is dealing
with understanding.

00:14:03.990 --> 00:14:08.160
For instance, I'm a non-native
English-speaking person.

00:14:08.160 --> 00:14:13.510
I'm from Germany,
and I have sometimes struggled

00:14:13.510 --> 00:14:18.530
to understand others when they
don't speak in a clear voice,

00:14:18.530 --> 00:14:25.900
or if they are talking really
fast, or have a strong dialect

00:14:25.900 --> 00:14:27.960
when they are speaking English.

00:14:27.960 --> 00:14:34.620
And so it is really difficult for me
to process what someone is saying,

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:39.290
or to understand what
the person is saying.

00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:50.180
Yes, that's the cognitive challenges
on the language barrier basis are.

00:14:51.530 --> 00:14:58.890
Also, someone with different
backgrounds has also difficulties

00:14:58.890 --> 00:15:07.900
to grasp the environment, and also
maybe distracted by the environment.

00:15:08.540 --> 00:15:12.830
So that is also the
challenge someone faces.

00:15:15.830 --> 00:15:19.030
And that's why visibility matters.

00:15:20.340 --> 00:15:23.690
It’s just not a phrase.

00:15:23.690 --> 00:15:28.870
I'm really advocating for
visibility in and why it matters,

00:15:28.870 --> 00:15:31.820
and representation
matters, It's a movement.

00:15:31.820 --> 00:15:39.200
And I like it also to be a call
of action, that we are rooting

00:15:39.200 --> 00:15:46.660
for those facing those challenges,
and we also want to create awareness

00:15:46.660 --> 00:15:51.020
so that someone gets more
empathy and understanding.

00:15:51.020 --> 00:15:55.800
And also to reducing the
stigma and the misconceptions

00:15:55.800 --> 00:16:01.280
around invisible health conditions.

00:16:01.280 --> 00:16:09.280
And also illuminating the pathways
where judgment hopefully fades away.

00:16:15.240 --> 00:16:22.050
But also to ensure that we
tailor our accommodations

00:16:22.050 --> 00:16:28.070
as WordPress event organizers,
and also fostering participation

00:16:28.070 --> 00:16:30.460
and contribution to those events.

00:16:34.340 --> 00:16:38.030
How we can accommodate
during a WordPress event

00:16:38.030 --> 00:16:42.140
like the WP Accessibility,
for instance.

00:16:42.140 --> 00:16:45.530
The organizing team did
a great job to make it

00:16:45.530 --> 00:16:49.670
as inclusive and
accessible as possible.

00:16:49.670 --> 00:16:57.190
That’s because they listen to
the challenges someone faces

00:16:57.190 --> 00:17:03.550
while attending,
but also participating on an event.

00:17:05.860 --> 00:17:12.350
This is also a space where
diverse voices aren't just heard,

00:17:12.350 --> 00:17:19.610
but also amplified, and it's not
just a concept, but also a living,

00:17:19.610 --> 00:17:22.470
breathing entity.

00:17:24.690 --> 00:17:30.790
Empowerment isn't just a gift we
offer; it's a space we create,

00:17:30.790 --> 00:17:34.870
where every member of our
community can sense the power

00:17:34.870 --> 00:17:38.600
of their truth and their
own yielding potential.

00:17:41.140 --> 00:17:44.717
This is why I think
it's very important

00:17:44.718 --> 00:17:47.490
that we empower our attendees,

00:17:47.490 --> 00:17:55.330
and that we also are
empathetic about it, to learn,

00:17:55.330 --> 00:17:58.980
and be also open-minded
to learn more about it.

00:18:00.350 --> 00:18:06.640
When we think about
invisible conditions.

00:18:06.640 --> 00:18:10.960
I like to transition to an analogy.

00:18:10.960 --> 00:18:17.280
I find it really simple,
because it compares as a bridge

00:18:17.280 --> 00:18:21.260
between the tangible and
intangible, and the seen and unseen.

00:18:24.300 --> 00:18:29.470
Invisible disabilities
are like a Wi-Fi signal.

00:18:29.470 --> 00:18:33.760
Picture this: You walk into a
room, your device in one hand,

00:18:33.760 --> 00:18:37.930
and there are no visible cords,
no tangible connections yet,

00:18:37.930 --> 00:18:41.120
In the silence and
in the invisibility,

00:18:41.120 --> 00:18:47.380
there's a powerful signal enabling
a communication, connection,

00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:48.440
and interaction.

00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:50.730
But do you see it?

00:18:52.030 --> 00:18:53.560
Do you see it really?

00:18:53.560 --> 00:18:54.950
Can you grasp it?

00:18:54.950 --> 00:18:55.950
Can you grab it?

00:18:57.380 --> 00:19:03.290
Just like Wi-Fi, invisible
disabilities are in our spaces,

00:19:03.290 --> 00:19:05.970
in our communities, in our events.

00:19:05.970 --> 00:19:11.180
And they may not be seen,
but they are deeply felt.

00:19:11.180 --> 00:19:18.290
And they may not be heard, but they
are profoundly impacting experiences

00:19:18.290 --> 00:19:21.530
and interaction,
and also engagement.

00:19:25.210 --> 00:19:25.960
Think about it.

00:19:25.960 --> 00:19:30.450
We don't question the existence
or the impact of a Wi-Fi signal,

00:19:32.230 --> 00:19:34.850
even if it's invisible.

00:19:34.850 --> 00:19:39.530
But we acknowledge it's presence,
and we adapt our actions

00:19:39.530 --> 00:19:44.730
and our spaces, but also our
technologies to handle the power

00:19:44.730 --> 00:19:49.590
of a Wi-Fi signal,
and to facilitate a connection,

00:19:49.590 --> 00:19:52.290
and to bridge distances.

00:19:52.290 --> 00:19:57.760
Similarly, the invisibility
of a certain disability

00:19:57.760 --> 00:20:02.790
should not negate our
existence or their existence

00:20:02.790 --> 00:20:04.650
or dilute their significance.

00:20:06.210 --> 00:20:10.830
So acknowledging that
invisible disabilities

00:20:10.830 --> 00:20:17.850
or invisible conditions exist,
and that we accommodate this

00:20:17.850 --> 00:20:22.340
because they're there even
if we are not on the surface.

00:20:27.840 --> 00:20:31.590
It is crucial that we ground our
understanding and empathy in numbers.

00:20:34.090 --> 00:20:41.700
I did a short research and I
found that one 1.3 billion people,

00:20:43.910 --> 00:20:49.960
about 16% of the global population,
are living with a severe disability.

00:20:51.380 --> 00:20:55.380
And even if each number of
this statistics is a person

00:20:55.380 --> 00:21:00.070
and individual with
experiences and challenges,

00:21:00.070 --> 00:21:05.350
and the contributions are as
diverse as they are significant,

00:21:05.350 --> 00:21:09.840
it's difficult to understand
that they are not visible.

00:21:11.780 --> 00:21:14.780
Also, when we think about
disabilities, the image

00:21:14.780 --> 00:21:16.700
of a wheelchair often prevails.

00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:20.020
And it's a visible symbol.

00:21:20.020 --> 00:21:27.090
We are presenting accessibility
by presenting it with iconography

00:21:27.090 --> 00:21:33.850
of a wheelchair, but it represents
only 2% of people with disabilities.

00:21:35.050 --> 00:21:40.160
The overwhelming majority
are a full 80% grappling

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:42.860
with invisible disabilities.

00:21:42.860 --> 00:21:49.650
And they also navigate a world where
their challenges, even though unseen,

00:21:49.650 --> 00:21:55.150
are as real and as impactful
as any visible disability.

00:21:56.960 --> 00:22:01.890
Yes, many of them are active
in the WordPress community.

00:22:01.890 --> 00:22:05.230
They are developers,
designers, users, contributors,

00:22:05.230 --> 00:22:11.820
and they enrich our community
with their skills, insights,

00:22:11.820 --> 00:22:12.820
and perspectives.

00:22:13.800 --> 00:22:18.240
Their invisible disabilities are
not barriers to their contributions,

00:22:18.240 --> 00:22:23.110
but they are also aspects
of their identity.

00:22:23.110 --> 00:22:25.792
And they also deserve
acknowledgement,

00:22:25.793 --> 00:22:28.130
understanding, and accommodation.

00:22:33.710 --> 00:22:37.900
As we move forward,
let's take a moment to delve

00:22:37.900 --> 00:22:43.170
into the specific types of
invisible health conditions.

00:22:44.630 --> 00:22:48.370
While the spectrum is
really vast and diverse,

00:22:48.370 --> 00:22:54.090
we will also focus on a select
to provide you a glimpse

00:22:54.090 --> 00:22:56.220
of the experiences.

00:22:58.790 --> 00:23:06.790
For this example, I picked some
well-known conditions like MECFS,

00:23:09.030 --> 00:23:16.190
Long COVID, CPTSD,
ADHD and Autism Spectrum Disorders.

00:23:16.190 --> 00:23:20.930
Each of these conditions,
even though invisible as profound,

00:23:20.930 --> 00:23:25.920
they have an impact on the life
of everyone who's facing them.

00:23:25.920 --> 00:23:30.570
And I just want to emphasize that
this is not an exhaustive list.

00:23:30.570 --> 00:23:35.102
The spectrum of invisible
health conditions is diverse

00:23:35.103 --> 00:23:36.750
as humanity itself.

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:42.480
And each individual experience is
unique and shaped by the interplay

00:23:42.480 --> 00:23:47.470
of their condition, and environment,
and personal resilience.

00:23:47.470 --> 00:23:53.110
I would like to talk
first about MECFS.

00:23:53.110 --> 00:23:58.860
It's a topic close to my heart
because I'm currently also suffering

00:23:58.860 --> 00:24:00.370
on that.

00:24:00.370 --> 00:24:08.370
And it's the abbreviation of
myalgic encephalomyelitis,

00:24:08.570 --> 00:24:10.880
or chronic fatigue syndrome.

00:24:10.880 --> 00:24:16.630
And it's also a condition
characterized by really heavy fatigue

00:24:16.630 --> 00:24:21.010
that you can't accommodate
with more sleep.

00:24:22.200 --> 00:24:27.510
And this deep exhaustion,
what you're facing,

00:24:27.510 --> 00:24:30.760
and this is also a
physical discomfort.

00:24:31.820 --> 00:24:36.770
Imagine a fatigue that
is so intense that it’s

00:24:36.770 --> 00:24:40.370
as if gravity itself
is pulling you down,

00:24:40.370 --> 00:24:46.020
and also making every step and every
thought as a monumental effort.

00:24:46.020 --> 00:24:52.630
For instance, when I had a
flare-up, I even couldn't work

00:24:52.630 --> 00:24:56.760
from the bath to the bathroom
without excruciating pain.

00:24:56.760 --> 00:25:04.750
And it was really difficult to
accommodate my daily existence,

00:25:04.750 --> 00:25:05.520
for instance.

00:25:05.520 --> 00:25:11.740
I'm really glad I'm doing better
now, but it's really hard

00:25:11.740 --> 00:25:16.040
to accommodate those,
and imagine that translating

00:25:18.680 --> 00:25:24.040
to a WordCamp attendance,
or a Meetup attendance in person,

00:25:24.040 --> 00:25:28.780
but also attending to a virtual
event like the WP Accessibility Day,

00:25:28.780 --> 00:25:34.540
which is 24 hours a day,
and you want to learn a lot,

00:25:34.540 --> 00:25:37.940
but you can't sit for a long
time with this condition.

00:25:38.980 --> 00:25:43.190
The same spectrum also
fits in the Long COVID.

00:25:44.350 --> 00:25:52.350
It is also known like a neurologic
effect similar to MECFS,

00:25:54.700 --> 00:26:02.400
where they also have symptoms
persisting for weeks or even months.

00:26:03.650 --> 00:26:07.633
It’s like a ghost of an illness.

00:26:11.410 --> 00:26:14.743
When you're walking
alongside a person

00:26:14.744 --> 00:26:17.820
and you can't see it on their face.

00:26:19.340 --> 00:26:25.320
The same goes also for complex
post-traumatic stress disorder.

00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:33.060
For instance, someone who has
faced several traumatic events.

00:26:35.470 --> 00:26:40.560
That can also lead to
certain chronic diseases,

00:26:40.560 --> 00:26:45.990
and affect the mental health,
and your emotional regulation,

00:26:45.990 --> 00:26:47.430
but also relationships.

00:26:50.220 --> 00:26:55.180
The same goes also for ADHD,
known as attention deficit

00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:57.070
hyperactivity disorder.

00:26:57.070 --> 00:27:04.730
And ADHD is previously more
known from boys or young boys.

00:27:04.730 --> 00:27:12.730
But recent research shows that
also women have a form of ADHD,

00:27:13.890 --> 00:27:20.270
where the hyperactivity part is
more related in the thought process.

00:27:20.270 --> 00:27:21.920
And it's overwhelming.

00:27:21.920 --> 00:27:27.340
You have to think about every
step you do to fulfill a task.

00:27:27.340 --> 00:27:35.340
And it also is a whirlwind
of thoughts, ideas, impulses,

00:27:35.350 --> 00:27:38.130
but also you get easily distracted.

00:27:38.130 --> 00:27:46.130
So when someone enters a room,
you're seeing it in your periphery,

00:27:46.720 --> 00:27:52.060
or you're hearing some
noises, or a dog is barking

00:27:52.060 --> 00:27:55.350
and you're already distracted.

00:27:56.430 --> 00:28:03.650
And it can have a toll on your
cognitive ability to understand

00:28:03.650 --> 00:28:06.010
what someone is just telling.

00:28:08.930 --> 00:28:12.930
Lastly, I just also want to
include the autism spectrum.

00:28:14.310 --> 00:28:19.795
There's sensory experiences
like social interaction

00:28:19.796 --> 00:28:23.199
that can be complex.

00:28:23.200 --> 00:28:26.832
And this also are health challenges

00:28:26.833 --> 00:28:29.380
where someone doesn't
have the ability

00:28:29.380 --> 00:28:37.030
to understand social cues,
or sarcasm, or a twink with the eye

00:28:37.030 --> 00:28:38.130
or something like that.

00:28:40.000 --> 00:28:45.220
Also the receptivity or
behavior someone may have needs

00:28:45.220 --> 00:28:50.870
to have a clear structure, where
they can go, what they can achieve.

00:28:53.120 --> 00:28:57.140
Each of these conditions,
even if they are invisible

00:28:57.140 --> 00:29:01.740
to the broader
audience, they are real.

00:29:01.740 --> 00:29:06.390
And those conditions shape
the lives and the experiences

00:29:06.390 --> 00:29:11.140
and contributions of many
in our WordPress community.

00:29:11.140 --> 00:29:16.010
I'm an advocate for inclusivity.

00:29:16.010 --> 00:29:19.850
And I’d like you to remember
that every step we take

00:29:19.850 --> 00:29:24.030
to accommodate and understand,
and support individuals

00:29:24.030 --> 00:29:29.320
with invisible health conditions is
a step toward a WordPress community

00:29:29.320 --> 00:29:35.970
that is truly diverse, inclusive, and
also makes someone feel belonging,

00:29:37.200 --> 00:29:44.510
and offers equitable ways to enter
the community and stay active

00:29:44.510 --> 00:29:45.510
in the community.

