are doing a good job?

00:45:00.900 --> 00:45:02.590
 BIRGIT: Thank you
for this great question.

00:45:03.660 --> 00:45:09.220
As I already mentioned,
there are ways to maybe survey,

00:45:10.410 --> 00:45:16.490
and pre-event organization
about kinds of disabilities.

00:45:16.490 --> 00:45:23.120
We need to be aware of the anonymity,
but also maybe privacy, GDPR.

00:45:23.120 --> 00:45:26.630
It is a sensitive topic to ask for.

00:45:26.630 --> 00:45:33.510
Not everyone is open to share
this, which is absolutely fine.

00:45:33.510 --> 00:45:40.220
But we are currently on
the WordPress Ecosystem

00:45:40.220 --> 00:45:44.780
and the DIB working group,
and we are currently working

00:45:44.780 --> 00:45:52.780
on facilitating a survey or offering
a survey to better understand

00:45:53.530 --> 00:45:57.480
how we can accommodate the
invisible disabilities.

00:45:59.130 --> 00:46:00.540
 SAMYUKTHA: That’s nice to know.

00:46:01.810 --> 00:46:08.210
Next question was from an Anonymous
attendee: You mentioned Long COVID,

00:46:08.210 --> 00:46:12.060
and I noticed the US
Center for Disease Control

00:46:12.060 --> 00:46:16.170
has increased the percentage
of people who have disabilities

00:46:16.170 --> 00:46:22.360
from 25% in 2019 to 27% now.

00:46:22.360 --> 00:46:25.090
Do you think that might
be due to Long COVID,

00:46:25.090 --> 00:46:27.870
or is there another explanation?

00:46:29.600 --> 00:46:31.490
 BIRGIT: Thank you
for this question.

00:46:31.490 --> 00:46:35.117
I'm not a research expert in that,

00:46:35.118 --> 00:46:39.490
